/wiki/Nils_Eekhoff: Nils Eekhoff ( born 23 January 1998 ) is a Dutch cyclist who rides for . In August 2019 , Eekhoff joined UCI WorldTeam as a stagiaire for the second half of the season .
/wiki/Development_Team_Sunweb: Development Team Sunweb is a German UCI Continental team founded in 2017 .
/wiki/Robert-Jon_McCarthy: Robert-Jon McCarthy ( born 30 March 1994 ) is an Irish , naturalized Australian , road cyclist . He was born in Cork and moved to Australia with his family when he was 14 . McCarthy won the third stage at the 2014 Herald Sun Tour . McCarthy also won the first stage at the 2014 Rás Tailteann .
/wiki/JLT\u2013Condor: JLT-Condor ( ) was a British UCI continental cycling team . They were previously Rapha Condor-recycling.co.uk following a merger between the recycling.co.uk Pro Cycling Team and the original RaphaCondor team at the end of 2007 .
/wiki/Alexander_Kamp: Alexander Kamp Egested ( born 14 December 1993 ) is a Danish cyclist , who currently rides for UCI Professional Continental team .
/wiki/Team_Waoo: Team Waoo is a UCI Continental team founded in 2012 and based in Denmark . It participates in UCI Continental Circuits races . In July 2016 Bjarne Riis and former Saxo Bank CEO Lars Seier announced that they had taken the team over and renamed it Team Virtu Pro-Veloconcept , with the intention of it functioning as the development team for a planned UCI WorldTeam . On 11 September 2017 the team changed its name into Team Virtu Cycling , after a new owner , Jan Bech Andersen , had bought one third of the shares . In July 2018 , the name changed again to Team Waoo .
/wiki/Filippo_Fortin: Filippo Fortin ( born 1 February 1989 in Venice ) is an Italian professional road and track cyclist , who currently rides for UCI Professional Continental team .
/wiki/Felbermayr\u2013Simplon_Wels: Felbermayr-Simplon Wels ( UCI team code : RSW ) is a UCI Continental team founded in 2004 . It is based in Austria and it participates in UCI Continental Circuits races .
/wiki/Du\u0161an_Rajovi\u0107: Dušan Rajović ( born 19 November 1997 , Kraljevo , Serbia ) is a Serbian cyclist riding for . From 2020 he will be part of Delko-Marseille Provence .
/wiki/Adria_Mobil_(cycling_team): Adria Mobil ( UCI team code : ADR ) is a Continental cycling team founded in 1972 ( as continental team from 2005 ) . It is based in Novo Mesto , Slovenia and it participates in UCI Continental Circuits races .
/wiki/Josef_\u010cern\u00fd_(cyclist): Josef Černý ( born 11 May 1993 ) is a Czech professional racing cyclist , who currently rides for UCI WorldTeam . In May 2019 , he was named in the startlist for the 2019 Giro d'Italia .
/wiki/Elkov\u2013Kasper: Elkov-Kasper ( UCI Code : ELK ) is a UCI Continental road bicycle racing team based in Czech Republic and participates in UCI Europe Tour . The sponsors of the team are Elkov , an electrical company , and Kasper , a steel manufacturer . The team was one of the best cycling teams before the lifting of the Iron Curtain . The team became professional in 2000 . The best known riders for the team were Alois Kaňkovský and Tomáš Bucháček . For the 2008 season the German sprinter André Schulze came from the Wiesenhof team and also Czech cyclist Ondřej Sosenka , a former World Hour Record holder , joined the team .
/wiki/Daniel_Auer: Daniel Auer ( born 26 October 1994 ) is an Austrian cyclist riding for .
/wiki/WSA_KTM_Graz: WSA KTM Graz is a UCI Continental team founded in 2011 and based in Austria . It participates in UCI Continental Circuits races .
/wiki/Tom_Wirtgen: Tom Wirtgen ( born 4 March 1996 in Dippach ) is a Luxembourgish cyclist , who currently rides for UCI Professional Continental team .
/wiki/Wallonie\u2013Bruxelles_Developmen: The Wallonie-Bruxelles Development Team is a Belgian UCI continental team founded in 201 . It participates in UCI Continental Circuits races .
/wiki/Asbj\u00f8rn_Kragh_Andersen: Asbjørn Kragh Andersen ( born 9 April 1992 ) is a Danish cyclist , who currently rides for UCI WorldTeam . He is the older brother of Søren Kragh Andersen , also a professional cyclist , with .
/wiki/Jan_B\u00e1rta: Jan Bárta ( born 7 December 1984 ) is a professional Czech road cyclist , currently riding for .
